<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHall2004">Hall, Michael J.W. (2004). "Incompleteness of trajectory-based interpretations of quantum mechanics". <i>Journal of Physics a Mathematical and General</i> <b>37</b>: 9549. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088%2F0305-4470%2F37%2F40%2F015" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088%2F0305-4470%2F37%2F40%2F015" rel="nofollow">10.1088/0305-4470/37/40/015</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/ArXiv" title="ArXiv">arΧiv</a>:<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0406054" class="extiw" title="arxiv:quant-ph/0406054">quant-ph/0406054</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Incompleteness+of+trajectory-based+interpretations+of+quantum+mechanics&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Physics+a+Mathematical+and+General&amp;rft.aulast=Hall&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael+J.W.&amp;rft.au=Hall%2C+Michael+J.W.&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=37&amp;rft.pages=9549&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1088%2F0305-4470%2F37%2F40%2F015&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Bohm_interpretation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (Demonstrates incompleteness of the Bohm interpretation in the face of fractal, differentialble-nowhere wave functions.)</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHolland1993">Holland, Peter R. (1993). <i>The Quantum Theory of Motion&#160;: An Account of the de Broglie-Bohm Causal Interpretation of Quantum Mechanics</i>. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521485436" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-48543-6</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Quantum+Theory+of+Motion+%3A+An+Account+of+the+de+Broglie-Bohm+Causal+Interpretation+of+Quantum+Mechanics&amp;rft.aulast=Holland&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter+R.&amp;rft.au=Holland%2C+Peter+R.&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.place=Cambridge&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-48543-6&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Bohm_interpretation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFNikolic2004">Nikolic, H. (2004). "Relativistic quantum mechanics and the Bohmian interpretation". <i>Foundations of Physics Letters</i> <b>18</b>: 549. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2Fs10702-005-1128-1" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2Fs10702-005-1128-1" rel="nofollow">10.1007/s10702-005-1128-1</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/ArXiv" title="ArXiv">arΧiv</a>:<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0406173" class="extiw" title="arxiv:quant-ph/0406173">quant-ph/0406173</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Relativistic+quantum+mechanics+and+the+Bohmian+interpretation&amp;rft.jtitle=Foundations+of+Physics+Letters&amp;rft.aulast=Nikolic&amp;rft.aufirst=H.&amp;rft.au=Nikolic%2C+H.&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=18&amp;rft.pages=549&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1007%2Fs10702-005-1128-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Bohm_interpretation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFPasson2004">Passon, Oliver (2004). <i>Why isn't every physicist a Bohmian?</i>. <a href="/wiki/ArXiv" title="ArXiv">arΧiv</a>:<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0412119" class="extiw" title="arxiv:quant-ph/0412119">quant-ph/0412119</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Why+isn%27t+every+physicist+a+Bohmian%3F&amp;rft.aulast=Passon&amp;rft.aufirst=Oliver&amp;rft.au=Passon%2C+Oliver&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Bohm_interpretation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFSanzF._Borondo2003">Sanz, A. S.; F. Borondo (2003). "A Bohmian view on quantum decoherence". <i>The European Physical Journal D</i> <b>44</b>: 319. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1140%2Fepjd%2Fe2007-00191-8" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1140%2Fepjd%2Fe2007-00191-8" rel="nofollow">10.1140/epjd/e2007-00191-8</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/ArXiv" title="ArXiv">arΧiv</a>:<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0310096" class="extiw" title="arxiv:quant-ph/0310096">quant-ph/0310096</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=A+Bohmian+view+on+quantum+decoherence&amp;rft.jtitle=The+European+Physical+Journal+D&amp;rft.aulast=Sanz&amp;rft.aufirst=A.+S.&amp;rft.au=Sanz%2C+A.+S.&amp;rft.au=F.+Borondo&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.volume=44&amp;rft.pages=319&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1140%2Fepjd%2Fe2007-00191-8&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Bohm_interpretation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFSanz2005">Sanz, A.S. (2005). "A Bohmian approach to quantum fractals". <i>J. Phys. A: Math. Gen.</i> <b>38</b>: 319. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088%2F0305-4470%2F38%2F26%2F013" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088%2F0305-4470%2F38%2F26%2F013" rel="nofollow">10.1088/0305-4470/38/26/013</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=A+Bohmian+approach+to+quantum+fractals&amp;rft.jtitle=J.+Phys.+A%3A+Math.+Gen.&amp;rft.aulast=Sanz&amp;rft.aufirst=A.S.&amp;rft.au=Sanz%2C+A.S.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.volume=38&amp;rft.pages=319&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1088%2F0305-4470%2F38%2F26%2F013&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Bohm_interpretation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (Describes a Bohmian resolution to the dilemma posed by non-differentiable wave functions.)</li>
